<subSubSection id="684D2B674BF586054E99F1B20A15FBDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D0CFE575E6757A15E501882F5842A451" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="ACDD983D269FA04BC2CAE296FA5A831E" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina fulvifacies" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvifacies">Platensina fulvifacies</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1941: 71. Type locality Lonaula, Maharashtra, India.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A3A4354FB0FC2AC9D9CE2439CA3BBAB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="020081E5750DA9B7BC77086B6892B2D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BEBE489236DC528908C13085EF4C763" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A0A8B121B5B145604F7F4CE00FDA825A" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. acrostacta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrostacta">
<emphasis id="C144D91A39DC50D003324889742837E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. acrostacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be differentiated primarily by the yellow face in males and larger basal spot in cell dm. Specimens were not available for study but photographs of both sexes have been examined: 2♂, 2♀, India: Rajasthan, Jodhpur District, 10 km SW Jodhpur, Machia Safari Pk, Malaise in dry wash 29.II-5.III.2008, 300 m, 
<geoCoordinate id="7C11CB51171592D6F1A4F9D7CD0E2101" degrees="26" direction="north" minutes="18.60" orientation="latitude" precision="9" value="26.31">26°18.60'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="16C139824F33E31F0C18C3501204A0AE" degrees="72" direction="east" minutes="58.71" orientation="longitude" precision="9" value="72.9785">72°58.71'E</geoCoordinate>
(in California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, California, USA).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="36DB4A6D47F11297FFE0925B0FFB962A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2E2068E395ADBA8CD9E7C82ACBF503DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1AB2E6239498F6BD6E3CD6EC3AD51201" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">This endemic Indian species is known only from Maharashtra and Rajasthan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
